							li The implemented scheme of closed water supply and sanitation at the treatment facilities of JSC Taneco provided 100% return to the production of treated wastewater, which allowed saving 7.62 million m3 of water in 2022 by excluding its consumption from the Kama River
							li The consumption of river water for production needs has been reduced by 3.7 million m3 due to the use of recycled water obtained by changing the supply scheme of Togliattikauchuk LLC water circulation unit, reconstruction of the main underground water pipeline for river water supply
							li Due to technological solutions used at the facilities for the preparation of co-produced water during the extraction of SVO, the use of fresh water in 2022 was optimized to reach 4.7 million m3, from 2018 – about 15 million m3
						h2 WATER DISPOSAL
						p Improvement of wastewater quality is one of the important objectives of the environmental safety program. The Company conducts regular monitoring of wastewater quality. Wastewater from production processes is sent to treatment facilities in accordance with the standards established by Russian legislation. The Company's laboratories as well as independent accredited organizations monitor compliance with the established standards.


