					.dmpage-quote
						|  In 2022, the TATNEFT Group achieved a 26% reduction in wastewater disposal.

					.dmpage-text

						p Investment projects for technological re-equipment of production are implemented, measures are taken to comply with the standards for the content of pollutants in wastewater, to maintain the territory of wastewater disposal sites and places in proper sanitary and ecological condition in order to ensure the regulatory level of wastewater treatment and the complete exclusion of the discharge of contaminated wastewater into the environment. 
						p In order to improve the quality of mechanical wastewater treatment of Tolyattikauchuk LLC, two radial primary settling tanks were reconstructed at the industrial wastewater neutralization and treatment plant and a system of reagent treatment of incoming wastewater was introduced. To improve the quality of aftertreatment, the drum nets were replaced at the industrial wastewater neutralization and treatment plant.
						p Wastewater was diverted to municipal sewerage organizations (transferred to a third party after use) – 4.9 million m3 (a decrease of 5% is due to the exit of the tire business from the perimeter of the TATNEFT Group.